cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SI, cs.PF 

This paper deals with the interference in wireless ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of the temporal and spatial correlation of the interference, which is a topic related to information theory and signal processing. Hence, cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category. Moreover, the paper uses a Poisson point process to model the node distribution, which is a topic related to mathematics and statistics. Therefore, cs.MA (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of interference on routing, which is a topic related to performance evaluation and optimization. Hence, cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category.
